               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Incipits and headings of some texts; short postscript to the Gospel of Matthew; total number of the chapters for an individual Gospel below the “tituli”; chapter numbers and titles in the margins; parts of the Canon tables; (elements of) the Ethiopic numerals; elements of the punctuation signs; chi-rho and coronis signes.&#xD;
&#xD;
On the incipit page of each Gospel and at the beginning of the Letter of Eusebius to Carpianus, a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
